Analysis.name: Spectacle independence for intermediate vision
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: The only information about randomization methods is a statement that the study is randomized. "There were no significant differences between the two investigated groups regarding age, gender and ocular pathology".
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: There is no information on whether a blinding process was implemented. No changes from the assigned intervention were reported or suspected. No detailed information on plan analysis.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: There is no information on whether a blinding process was implemented.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: There is no protocol trial; however, all reported results for the outcome domain correspond to the methods section.

Analysis.name: Frequency of any ocular AE
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: The only information about randomization methods is a statement that the study is randomized. "There were no significant differences between the two investigated groups regarding age, gender and ocular pathology".
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: There is no information on whether a blinding process was implemented. No changes from the assigned intervention were reported or suspected. It seems that all participants were included in the analysis and were maintained in their assignment group.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: There is no information on the use of structured questionnaires or validated tools. There is no information on whether a blinding process was implemented and/or a detailed description of the outcome measurement. Since the outcome corresponds to a patient-reported one, in the setting of a non-blinding study, it is likely to be influenced by the knowledge of the intervention received.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: There is no protocol trial; however, all reported results for the outcome domain correspond to the methods section. All eligible reported results and analyses for the outcome domain correspond to all intended outcome measurements.

Analysis.name: Spectacle independence for intermediate vision
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: The only information about randomization methods is the statement that the study is randomized. Participants in the first group were older than in the second group, and presbyopia is a progressive age-related disorder; therefore, the severity of the disease may be different.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: There is no information on whether a blinding process was implemented. It seems that there were no changes from the assigned intervention. All participants were analyzed.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: There is no information on whether a blinding process was implemented.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: There is no protocol trial; however, all reported results for the outcome domain correspond to the methods section.
